==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Secretiveness
<hw>Se*cret"ive*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of
being secretive; disposition or tendency to conceal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Phren.)</fld> <def>The faculty or propensity which
impels to reserve, secrecy, or concealment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secretly</ent>⟦br⟧
